The book: End of Days" by Sylvia Browne was published in 2008, more than a decade before the coronavirus outbreak in Wuhan, China in 2019.
The Facebook post circulating the claim: with specific sentences underlined or circled in orange, suggesting a prediction of a severe illness spreading globally in 2020.
Fact: checkers used Google Books to search the text of "End of Days" for references to "Wuhan" and "Wuhan-400" but found no such mentions.
The reference to: Wuhan-400" actually comes from a different book, "The Eyes of Darkness" by Dean Koontz, published in 1981, which describes a fictional virus with a 100% fatality rate, unlike the real coronavirus outbreak.
